OL,3,CMPs call for local authorities to be
OL,4,Chanded control of council tax
OL,6,F"Government in England is
OL,7,Fovercentralised. The current financial
OL,8,Fpressures on local government are also
OL,9,Fdriven largely by mandatory, high-
OL,10,Fcost, demand-led services, such as
OL,11,Fsocial care and special educational
OL,12,Fneeds or disabilities, where councils
OL,13,Fhave little control over these needs.
OL,15,F"Councils are trapped in a
OL,16,Fstraitjacket by central government,
OL,17,Fwith local authorities lacking the
OL,18,Fflexibility or control to devise
OL,19,Fcreative, long-term, preventative
OL,20,Fsolutions which could offer better
OL,21,Fvalue for money.
