OL,6,FResponding to the findings, the Local
OL,7,FGovernment Association (LGA) said the
OL,8,Ffindings provide further evidence of
OL,9,Fthe fragile state of local government
OL,10,Ffinances.
OL,12,FPete Marland, chair of the LGA's
OL,13,Feconomy and resources board, said:
OL,14,F"Greater financial certainty and a
OL,15,Fsimpler funding system are important.
OL,16,FHowever, all councils remain under
OL,17,Fpressure and face having to increase
OL,18,Fcouncil tax bills to try and protect
OL,19,Fservices at the same time as making
OL,20,Ffurther cutbacks.
